 Business Briefs

 Mumbai, Aug. 20: The foreign exchange (forex) reserves of the country rose by $1.738 billion for the week ended August 12 to $144.375 billion, according to the Reserve Bank of India?s weekly statistical supplement released here today. The rise in inflows is mainly due to the revaluation of international currencies, especially the US dollar, analysts said. The forex reserves over the past three weeks have increased by $6.82 billion.

 Chennai, Aug. 20: With stock markets trading at all-time high levels, the Securities and Exchange Board of India today cautioned small investors against the pitfalls and asked them to look for safer instruments such as mutual funds. ?Sebi is not in the business of advising investors. But, I would urge small investors to take informed decisions,? Sebi chairman M. Damodaran said.

 Mumbai, Aug. 20: Ashok Sinha has taken over as the chairman and managing director of Bharat Petroleum Corporation Ltd.




